 the technologies I cover (like ChromaDB, Ollama, or NVIDIA GPUs)?\n3. Or perhaps a misspelling of another term?\n\nLet me know how I can assist!', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'qwen3', 'created_at': '2026-07-04T00:10:15.8862911Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 2025135900, 'load_duration': 83552200, 'prompt_eval_count': 682, 'prompt_eval_duration': 38704000, 'eval_count': 280, 'eval_duration': 1898858000, 'logprobs': None, 'model_name': 'qwen3', 'model_provider': 'ollama'}, id='lc_run--019f2a76-25e4-7f63-bde4-9690cd9d5eb3-0', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 682, 'output_tokens': 280, 'total_tokens': 962}), HumanMessage(content='it is also called expedition 33', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='95d69c48-09fd-4e40-b450-ccc7799993c3'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'qwen3', 'created_at': '2026-07-04T00:10:41.6653435Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 3145488400, 'load_duration': 86172700, 'prompt_eval_count': 788, 'prompt_eval_duration': 225411000, 'eval_count': 408, 'eval_duration': 2794719000, 'logprobs': None, 'model_name': 'qwen3', 'model_provider': 'ollama'}, id='lc_run--019f2a76-8637-7d72-a3cd-10dc805e73c0-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'knowledge_search', 'args': {'question': 'Expedition 33'}, 'id': 'b160a4b9-87bd-48e3-98a4-07242a0e8869', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 788, 'output_tokens': 408, 'total_tokens': 1196}), ToolMessage(content='### Nodes\nNodes are Python functions that receive the current State and return a partial update to it.\nThe `chatbot` node invokes the LLM with the current message list. The `tools` node executes\nany tool calls that the LLM requested.\n\n---\n\n## FastAPI\nFastAPI is a modern Python web framework for building APIs. It uses Python type hints to\nautomatically validate request/response bodies (via Pydantic) and generate OpenAPI docs at /docs.\n\n---\n\n### Edges\n- `add_edge(A, B)` creates a fixed transition from node A to node B.\n- `add_conditional_edges(A, condition_fn)` lets the graph branch based on runtime output.\n- `tools_condition` is a built-in condition that routes to the `tools` node when the LLM\n  emits a tool call, or to END when it produces a final text response.', name='knowledge_search', id='714b1091-02d9-4a5c-8ea5-b80fc811e047', tool_call_id='b160a4b9-87bd-48e3-98a4-07242a0e8869'), AIMessage(content='I don\'t have information about "Expedition 33" in my knowledge base either. The search results you shared seem to relate to technical concepts like FastAPI, graph nodes, and tool execution workflows, which don\'t connect to "Clair obscure" or "Expedition 33."\n\nCould you provide more context or clarify what you\'re referring to? For example:\n- Is this related to a specific movie, book, scientific expedition, or technical project?\n- Did you mean a different term (e.g., "Expedition 33" vs. "Expedition 3.3")?\n\nLet me know how I can assist! 😊', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'qwen3', 'created_at': '2026-07-04T00:10:44.3959189Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 2709989200, 'load_duration': 88343000, 'prompt_eval_count': 1005, 'prompt_eval_duration': 33764000, 'eval_count': 371, 'eval_duration': 2583613000, 'logprobs': None, 'model_name': 'qwen3', 'model_provider': 'ollama'}, id='lc_run--019f2a76-9295-7952-86b9-be968cb958d8-0', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 1005, 'output_tokens': 371, 'total_tokens': 1376}), HumanMessage(content='is a videogame', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='fcfb9b42-3cb0-4900-b68d-d5b145463b04'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'qwen3', 'created_at': '2026-07-04T00:10:53.1614231Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 2198402800, 'load_duration': 89071700, 'prompt_eval_count': 1156, 'prompt_eval_du